<p>
The Singapore Post barcode specification, also known as the Singapore 4-State Barcode (4SB), is a linear barcode type developed by Singapore Post Limited (SingPost) for their postal services. It was developed to improve the efficiency and accuracy of mail processing and delivery in Singapore. This symbology was specifically designed to meet the requirements of the Singapore postal system and is widely used to execute domestic and international mail services, facilitating mail operations and reliable tracking.

<ul><li><b>Barcode Structure:</b> The Singapore Post barcode symbology utilizes a 4-state format&colon; bars, full bars, half bars, and tracker bars. These states encode postal information, including postal codes, sorting information, and delivery point identifiers.</li><li><b>Compact Size:</b> The Singapore Post barcode specification is designed to be compact, enabling efficient use of label space on mail items, envelopes, and packages.</li><li><b>Readability:</b> Such barcodes can be easily scannable by postal service providers using special scanning devices. This ensures accurate and timely processing of mail items.</li></ul><h4>Applications</h4><ul><li><b>Domestic Mail Services:</b> Singapore Post barcodes are widely used for domestic mail services, including letter post, parcels, and registered mail. It enables automated sorting, accurate routing, and efficient delivery across Singapore.</li><li><b>International Mail Services:</b> This barcode type is employed to process international mail items originating from Singapore. It assists in identifying the origin, destination, and relevant sorting information, facilitating smooth handling, and tracking across borders.</li><li><b>E-commerce and Cross-border Shipping:</b> The Singapore Post barcode specification is integrated into the shipping and labeling processes of e-commerce platforms to provide end-to-end visibility and tracking controls for cross-border shipments. It ensures reliable delivery and increases customer satisfaction.</li></ul><p>The unique structure and compact size of Singapore Post barcodes conform to the specific requirements of the Singapore postal system.
